"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-paris-olympics-dating-app-change-location-athlete-b1174228.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  News|World  Picture the scene, it is Friday night and you are swiping left and right on yourphonetrying to find someone to meet up with.  There is slim pickings so you give up hope.  But what if you swapped your usual scenery and transported yourself to alocationwhere there are a whole village of ridiculously fit athletes?  Well, clued up Londoners are cottoning onto a dating hack that will allow fast access to scores of eligible matches.  In case you have not guessed, they are doing this by changing their location ondating appstoParisin the hope of bagging themselves an athlete.  Tinder users popularised this trick at the 2018 Winter Olympicsand singletons are this are having another go this time around.  Influencer Sofia Elizabeth shared aTikTokvideo aboutchanging her dating app location to the Olympic Villagetothe north of Paris and now others are following suit, with thanks.  Speaking in her video, a user said: \\\"Whoever said to change your location to the 'Olympic Village' currently in Paris to match with an Olympian, I just wanna thank you from the bottom of my heart.\\\"  And Sofia again took to TikTok, to say she could not believe how things have taken off after she posted her tip. See here:  Tinder reportedly saidin July, there was been an almost 20 percent increase in swipes in France, and a 103 percent increase in\\u00a0Passport Mode\\u00a0(a paid feature to change your location) to sites like Paris.  The US, Brazil, and Turkey are the top origin countries where daters are using Passport Mode to change their location to France in the hope of findinglove.  And why not?  Olympians are strong, they are fit, and they are at the peak of their game\\u2026 which even led us to post ourmost crush-worthy Olympians of Paris 2024.  Just some of the athletes we can not get enough of include 22-year-old French springboard diver Jules Bouyer, US gymnast Sunisa Lee andItalian backstroke champion Thomas Ceccon.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"